WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:02.500
NARRATOR: Previously
on  Dawson's Creek...

00:02.500 --> 00:04.000
JEN:
I'm always up for a good party.

00:04.000 --> 00:07.834
Why don't we pick it up
from "God's promise
and warning"?

00:07.834 --> 00:09.875
Pacey, uh, you got a...

00:09.875 --> 00:13.166
I got an "A".
I got an "A", Andie,

00:13.166 --> 00:15.625
and I'm falling hopelessly
in love with you, Andie.

00:15.625 --> 00:18.458
You were with Jack,
you moved on, and you let go.

00:18.458 --> 00:21.458
So now I, in turn,
am letting you go.

00:21.458 --> 00:23.834
Dawson, is clearly over me.
I promise.

00:23.834 --> 00:26.458
Just as long as you're over him,
nothing else matters.

00:34.250 --> 00:36.667
PACEY: I can't believe
you made this whole thing
by yourself.

00:36.667 --> 00:37.834
Congratulations, Jack.

00:37.834 --> 00:39.417
Thanks.
I'm not completely done, though.

00:39.417 --> 00:42.208
I mean, I still have this
whole back section to paint.

00:42.208 --> 00:46.542
So I'm truly impressed
and-- and grateful.

00:46.917 --> 00:49.291
I'm still a little unclear
though as to
why you wanted this.

00:49.291 --> 00:51.375
You're not going to
blow it up or anything, are ya?

00:51.375 --> 00:54.125
No. No. There's
no asteroid in my movie.

00:54.125 --> 00:55.583
It's for aerial shots,
establishing.

00:55.583 --> 00:56.959
Just get the right lens
and the right light,

00:56.959 --> 01:00.041
and you've got the perfect,
quaint Creekside village.

01:00.041 --> 01:02.083
It's amazing what a little
camera trickery can do.

01:02.083 --> 01:03.667
Well,
if you guys will excuse me,

01:03.667 --> 01:06.375
I have a ton of homework
to do, including
Peterson's assignment,

01:06.375 --> 01:08.125
which I haven't
even started yet.

01:08.125 --> 01:09.250
Yeah. I haven't either.

01:09.250 --> 01:11.875
Pacey Witter is leaving
early to do homework.

01:11.875 --> 01:15.667
Ha! It's slightly
less believable than
an Enquirer  headline.

01:15.667 --> 01:17.458
Oh, yeah.
It's a disgusting habit.

01:17.458 --> 01:19.041
Ha!

01:19.041 --> 01:21.375
All right. Well, thanks,
guys, I'll see you later.

01:21.375 --> 01:22.375
No. I can stay.

01:22.375 --> 01:23.708
But I'm just gonna
do a test shot.

01:23.708 --> 01:26.375
No. It's ok. I'd like to see it.
It's all right.

01:26.375 --> 01:28.625
Ok. Cool.

01:32.500 --> 01:34.708
Well, ta-ta, gents.

01:35.500 --> 01:38.041
Don't stay up too late,
you know? It is a school night.

01:39.625 --> 01:41.166
Speaking as his closest friend,

01:41.166 --> 01:44.792
your sister has had quite
a profound influence on him.

01:45.291 --> 01:47.291
Yeah, well,
relationships will do that.

01:47.875 --> 01:48.917
Yeah.

01:52.417 --> 01:57.458
Sorry. I didn't mean that
the way that came out.

02:00.333 --> 02:01.792
Look, Jack--

02:01.792 --> 02:05.166
This hasn't exactly been
the easiest situation
for either of us,

02:05.166 --> 02:07.667
but your help
on this film has been
so significant,

02:07.667 --> 02:11.333
- I just...
- JACK: So we're cool?

02:11.333 --> 02:12.125
Yeah.

02:12.834 --> 02:14.708
So what's this Peterson
assignment about?

02:14.708 --> 02:15.792
Ah, a poem.

02:16.208 --> 02:18.000
He wants us to write
about something that's
critical to our being.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.792
Whatever. It's just
another assignment
I'm gonna screw up.

02:21.500 --> 02:23.417
It's a poem.
It can't be that hard.

02:24.291 --> 02:27.125
I read your script.
You're the expert writer here.

02:27.583 --> 02:29.834
Any advice as to how
to get to the good stuff?

02:29.834 --> 02:33.708
Um... Listen to yourself.

02:34.208 --> 02:35.667
Writing's about
opening up, you know?

02:35.959 --> 02:38.834
It's a chance to offer the world
a peek at that very private
part of yourself

02:38.834 --> 02:43.125
-that you otherwise just stifle.
-JACK: So just listen to myself?

02:43.125 --> 02:44.500
Yeah. I mean...

02:45.166 --> 02:46.750
You never know
what you'll hear.

02:47.667 --> 02:49.500
Could you do me a favor
and hit the lights?

02:49.500 --> 02:50.500
Oh, yeah.

02:58.333 --> 02:59.583
And there it is...

03:01.542 --> 03:04.792
It's your perfect
Creekside village.

