04:02.208 --> 04:03.333
MR. MILO: Pacey!

04:03.333 --> 04:05.542
Mr. Milo. Now,
before you say anything,

04:05.542 --> 04:08.041
I want you to know
I have the situation
under complete control.

04:08.041 --> 04:09.792
And what situation is that?

04:10.542 --> 04:12.750
Well, whichever of my
academic improprieties

04:12.750 --> 04:14.291
you were about
to make me aware of.

04:14.291 --> 04:16.708
"Improprieties"
is the wrong word.

04:16.708 --> 04:18.041
Try "kudos."

04:18.666 --> 04:21.041
I just received
the midterm reports

04:21.041 --> 04:23.250
for all of the students
on academic watch,

04:23.667 --> 04:28.000
and after removing
my jaw from the floor,
I came to see you.

04:28.750 --> 04:31.792
You posted three Bs, two As.

04:31.792 --> 04:33.375
What? That's impossible.

04:33.375 --> 04:34.917
One would think so.

04:36.792 --> 04:40.250
You know, I don't think
I've ever seen you
smile before, Mr. Milo.

04:40.250 --> 04:41.208
I'm liking this.

04:41.208 --> 04:42.291
The smiling thing,
I definitely like.

04:42.583 --> 04:45.750
Well, you just
keep up the good work,
Mr. Witter.

04:47.875 --> 04:48.750
Yes!

04:52.333 --> 04:54.875
- [ANDIE SQUEALS]
- Hey, lady!

04:59.917 --> 05:02.750
- Mm. What was that for?
- Just because.

05:03.875 --> 05:05.000
Uh, don't even.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.125
What? We can't
have a "just because"?

05:07.125 --> 05:10.125
Sure. In private,
but massive suck-face embraces

05:10.125 --> 05:12.500
are better left for bedrooms
and private sunsets.

05:13.250 --> 05:14.125
No offense.

05:14.125 --> 05:15.583
- None taken.
- None taken.

05:16.333 --> 05:17.041
Hey, guys.

05:17.458 --> 05:19.125
Jack, I was just wondering,
when do you think

05:19.125 --> 05:21.583
we can get started on the set
for the pageant scene?

05:21.583 --> 05:22.834
This weekend, if you want.

05:22.834 --> 05:25.458
Ok, great. I'll schedule
the shoot for the weekend after.

05:25.458 --> 05:26.708
[BELL RINGS]

05:28.875 --> 05:30.500
Well, I hate to be the stickler,

05:30.500 --> 05:32.166
but we are late
for an hour of hell.

05:32.166 --> 05:33.583
Yeah. You got your poem,
stickler?

05:33.583 --> 05:34.834
Of course!

05:34.834 --> 05:36.083
I gotta go with those guys.

05:36.083 --> 05:37.750
- Ok. Bye.
- Bye.

05:41.417 --> 05:44.834
So...
That was nice.

05:44.834 --> 05:46.250
What was nice?

05:46.250 --> 05:48.250
You and Jack
actually conversing.

05:48.834 --> 05:50.000
It was a surprise.

05:50.375 --> 05:52.500
Some people are capable
of moving beyond their

05:52.500 --> 05:55.250
petty longtime rivalries
to a higher ground.

05:55.250 --> 05:56.667
Yeah, right.

05:56.667 --> 05:58.750
If Jack wasn't doing
your movie, Dawson,

05:58.750 --> 06:00.417
he'd still be the enemy.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.125
Not true.

06:02.125 --> 06:04.041
You are so Hollywood.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.959
Across the crowded green,
he spots her.

06:10.959 --> 06:14.792
Stealthily, the lion
crosses and settles in
beside his prey:

06:14.792 --> 06:16.291
the helpless llama.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.041
Hey, Ty.

06:19.917 --> 06:20.875
Well, as far as I know,

06:21.375 --> 06:23.875
there have been
three phone messages to you
in this last week.

06:23.875 --> 06:26.708
Adorable phone messages
with my number included.

06:27.083 --> 06:30.166
So I was just wondering
why you haven't
returned any of them.

06:31.125 --> 06:33.750
You're on my
to-call list, Ty.

06:33.750 --> 06:35.542
Just working my way around.

06:36.125 --> 06:37.708
You know,
not to toot my own horn,

06:37.708 --> 06:40.250
but I could swear you
were into me that night
that we went out.

06:40.250 --> 06:42.458
Not to toot your
own horn or anything.

06:44.875 --> 06:46.333
It was the party, wasn't it?

06:47.417 --> 06:49.708
All that Bible-speak,
it freaked you out.

06:51.291 --> 06:53.625
Honestly? Yeah, it did.

06:53.959 --> 06:57.458
Jen, that's not all
that I am, all right?

06:57.458 --> 07:02.041
For your information,
I'm not some Bible-banging
dorkus mcforkus here.

07:02.917 --> 07:05.959
Ok, I'm sure
that you're not, Ty. It's just--

07:07.208 --> 07:09.625
Uh, ok,
obviously your religion

07:09.625 --> 07:11.792
is something that's
very important to you.

07:12.417 --> 07:15.542
I just see it as
an inevitable obstacle
in our relationship.

07:15.542 --> 07:17.583
Don't you think
that we should go out
on our first date

07:17.583 --> 07:19.583
before you map out
our entire future?

07:19.583 --> 07:22.125
Ty, you're sweet.
And you're funny.

07:23.083 --> 07:25.291
But you go to
these bible meetings
three times a week,

07:25.291 --> 07:27.417
and that's probably
how many times
I've been to church

07:27.417 --> 07:28.417
in the past ten years,

07:28.875 --> 07:32.500
so hopefully you
can understand why that
would present a problem

07:32.500 --> 07:35.750
with us being anything
more than just friends,
all right?

07:36.125 --> 07:39.542
See? That just goes to show
how little you know me.

07:40.959 --> 07:46.000
See? I'm not funny at all.
Look, I'm not giving up.

07:46.000 --> 07:47.250
Now, that's a shame.

07:47.250 --> 07:49.959
You know, I thought most women
admired persistence.

07:49.959 --> 07:52.542
Well, that just goes to show
how little you know about me.

07:52.542 --> 07:53.834
I'm not most women.

08:07.792 --> 08:11.250
Mr. Witter,
empty-handed, I presume?

08:11.250 --> 08:13.500
No. It was in here.
I mean, I had it at the locker.

08:13.500 --> 08:16.542
I just-- I must've...
left it right here in my binder.

08:20.458 --> 08:23.375
"Ode to the sports car."

08:23.375 --> 08:25.500
Yeah. Trust me.
They're more exciting
than Grecian urns.

08:25.500 --> 08:29.834
Experimenting
with cursive for the
first time, Mr. Witter?

08:29.834 --> 08:31.333
Listen, I worked hard on that.

08:31.333 --> 08:32.332
I'm sure.

08:32.332 --> 08:35.125
However, you
neglected penmanship,

08:35.125 --> 08:38.417
and presentation
is half the grade,

08:38.417 --> 08:41.917
so, as I see it,
you have two choices:

08:41.917 --> 08:44.875
you can bring
the poem in tomorrow,
written legibly

08:44.875 --> 08:47.500
and lose points
for handing it in late,

08:47.500 --> 08:52.166
or you can hand it in as it is,
and the highest grade you'll see

08:52.166 --> 08:54.792
will be your old friend,
the letter "D".

08:57.333 --> 09:00.917
- That's not fair.
- Fairness is overrated.

09:03.041 --> 09:05.917
Is it just me, or does that man
get meaner every day?

09:05.917 --> 09:07.250
It's not just you.

09:07.250 --> 09:10.166
Excuse me, Mr. McPhee?

09:10.166 --> 09:11.875
Uh, nothing.

09:13.041 --> 09:17.375
I trust that your poetry
assignment went well,
Mr. McPhee.

09:17.375 --> 09:19.583
We're all aware
of how critical it is

09:19.583 --> 09:22.625
to your deficient grade
in this class.

09:22.625 --> 09:25.917
- Sure. Yeah. It, um, went fine.
- Good!

09:26.708 --> 09:30.000
Then perhaps you would
like to read your poem
for the class.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.917
Um, you said that these poems
were just for you.

09:33.917 --> 09:37.041
I changed my mind.
These things happen.

09:37.375 --> 09:42.458
- Please, read us your poem.
- I'd really rather not.

09:43.417 --> 09:48.458
Mr. McPhee,
what you would rather do
is of no importance to me.

09:49.333 --> 09:51.667
If it's ok with you,
can I just hand it in?

09:51.667 --> 09:55.333
- Read the poem.
- Please. I don't--

09:55.333 --> 09:56.500
We're waiting.

10:11.208 --> 10:12.458
Um...

10:17.708 --> 10:18.875
"Today.

10:21.583 --> 10:24.792
"Today was a day
the world got smaller,

10:26.375 --> 10:27.708
"Darker...

10:31.083 --> 10:32.500
"I grew more afraid.

10:35.583 --> 10:37.750
Not of what I am,
but of what I..."

10:42.834 --> 10:44.291
Continue.

10:49.417 --> 10:50.542
Uh...

10:51.875 --> 10:53.458
"I grew more afraid...

10:55.500 --> 10:57.291
"Not of what I am,
but what I--

10:57.792 --> 10:59.083
"What I could be,

11:00.083 --> 11:02.542
"I loosen my collar
to take a breath,

11:03.291 --> 11:04.667
"My eyes fade...

11:06.375 --> 11:07.625
And I see..."

11:10.667 --> 11:11.917
"I see him...

11:13.875 --> 11:16.250
[VOICE STARTS TO CRACK]
The image of perfection."

11:19.458 --> 11:22.208
His frame strong,
his lips smooth..."

11:24.333 --> 11:26.875
"I keep thinking,
what am I so scared of?

11:28.375 --> 11:30.125
"And I wish I
could escape the pain,

11:30.125 --> 11:32.250
"But these thoughts,
they invade my head,

11:33.542 --> 11:35.166
"Bound to my memory...

11:36.625 --> 11:38.583
They're like shackles
of guilt."

11:42.000 --> 11:43.542
[WHIMPERING]

11:43.542 --> 11:46.041
"God, please set me free."
Excuse me.

11:51.708 --> 11:53.000
MR. PETERSON:
What are you doing?

11:53.000 --> 11:54.375
I'm gonna go see
if he's all right.

11:54.375 --> 11:55.792
You'll do nothing of the kind.
Sit down.

11:55.792 --> 11:58.834
- He was crying--
- I said sit down!

12:06.375 --> 12:08.959
Everyone,
open your books, please,

12:08.959 --> 12:12.542
to page 57, stanza 2.

12:23.583 --> 12:24.625
What are you doing?

12:24.625 --> 12:27.000
- Nothing.
- What?

12:27.000 --> 12:30.375
I'm just trying to
get a peek at your
secret online handle.

12:31.250 --> 12:33.875
What is it? Juicy Joan?
Perky Potter?

12:33.875 --> 12:35.458
What's yours--
Spielberg Stud?

12:35.458 --> 12:37.166
- No.
- BOY: Then he starts to cry.

12:37.166 --> 12:37.917
SECOND BOY: No way.

12:38.250 --> 12:40.000
No. I heard it from,
like, half the class.

12:40.000 --> 12:42.708
He's reading this poem,
and he is just crying.

12:42.708 --> 12:44.041
[LAUGHING]

12:44.041 --> 12:45.792
Wait. Who was this?

12:45.792 --> 12:47.333
Jack McPhee, the new kid.

12:47.959 --> 12:50.500
Peterson makes him
read his poem in class.

12:50.500 --> 12:52.083
He starts crying.

12:52.500 --> 12:53.583
FIRST BOY: No kidding?

12:53.583 --> 12:55.208
SECOND BOY:
Here's the best part...

12:55.208 --> 12:59.959
The poem, it's about a guy.
McPhee's a total homo.

12:59.959 --> 13:03.041
Ha! Total.
Like, no doubt.

13:14.375 --> 13:15.959
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

13:15.959 --> 13:17.125
Thank you.

13:17.917 --> 13:19.542
- Hi, Dawson.
- Hey.

13:19.959 --> 13:22.959
- Joey, hey, you got a second?
- Sure.

13:22.959 --> 13:26.959
Um...
Have you talked to Jack yet?

13:27.583 --> 13:29.792
Oh, we haven't really
talked about it yet. No.

13:29.792 --> 13:31.291
He's still pretty upset
about it.

13:31.291 --> 13:33.250
Yeah, I can imagine.

13:33.250 --> 13:35.583
Rumor mill's working overtime
on this one.

13:35.583 --> 13:37.625
I've heard about the incident
twice more.

13:37.625 --> 13:39.291
You've heard about it?
I've heard everything

13:39.291 --> 13:41.750
from Jack is seen
regularly wearing dresses
down Main Street

13:41.750 --> 13:45.417
to he's checked
into a monastery to deal
with his sexual ambivalence.

13:46.208 --> 13:47.792
You're being pretty flip
about this.

13:48.291 --> 13:50.917
Well, why not, Dawson?
I mean, it's all a big joke.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.000
Is it?

13:54.542 --> 13:57.291
- What are you insinuating?
- I'm not insinuating anything.

13:57.291 --> 14:00.083
I'm-- I'm just--
I'm concerned about you.

14:00.917 --> 14:02.500
What are you
trying to do, Dawson,

14:02.500 --> 14:05.625
give validity to
some ridiculous rumor
that Jack's gay?

14:05.625 --> 14:08.083
- No. Joey, I never said that.
- You pretty much did.

14:08.083 --> 14:10.125
All I'm trying to do is find out
what's going on.

14:10.125 --> 14:11.875
I would hope that
you know me well enough

14:11.875 --> 14:13.333
to know that my concern
is genuine.

14:13.333 --> 14:15.166
There's no need to be
so defensive about this.

14:15.166 --> 14:17.125
I'm not being defensive,
Dawson.

14:17.125 --> 14:19.500
Why don't we just say
what this conversation
is really about?

14:19.500 --> 14:22.583
Your passive aggressive way
of highlighting some flaw
in Jack

14:22.583 --> 14:24.166
that would get us to break up.

14:24.166 --> 14:25.542
That's way over the line.

14:25.542 --> 14:27.291
No, it's not.
From where I'm standing,

14:27.291 --> 14:29.000
I think
it's perfectly in bounds.

14:34.542 --> 14:37.333
"So in 1936,
the Stalin constitution
was adopted.

14:37.333 --> 14:39.708
"Communists
everywhere boasted
that the Soviet Union

14:39.708 --> 14:42.000
was now the most
democratic country
in the world."

14:42.000 --> 14:45.083
I'm gonna go down
to the ice house
and help them close up.

14:45.083 --> 14:46.250
I'll see ya later.

14:47.208 --> 14:48.333
Later, Jack.

14:50.250 --> 14:51.458
[DOOR SHUTS]

14:52.542 --> 14:56.917
- Boy, you were a bit frosty.
- Pardon?

14:58.041 --> 14:59.458
To Jack.
The guy's had a hard day,

14:59.458 --> 15:01.834
and you've hardly said
two words to him all afternoon.

15:02.959 --> 15:03.792
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:04.500 --> 15:06.750
Well, I don't understand
why he had to write
that poem to begin with.

15:06.750 --> 15:08.041
I mean, if he hadn't
written something

15:08.041 --> 15:10.250
that could have been so easily
misinterpreted, then--

15:10.250 --> 15:11.834
What? If he had
censored himself?

15:12.625 --> 15:14.000
Don't twist my words.

15:14.000 --> 15:17.083
Ok, look. I know Jack
better than you do, Pacey.

15:17.083 --> 15:19.125
And ever since we were kids,

15:19.125 --> 15:21.458
he's had this whole different
drummer thing going on,

15:21.458 --> 15:23.041
and not everybody gets it.

15:23.041 --> 15:25.083
He should have known better
than to expose himself

15:25.083 --> 15:27.083
to someone as venomous
as Peterson. That's all.

15:27.083 --> 15:29.542
Andie, I may be wrong here, but
I don't think guest starring in

15:29.542 --> 15:32.125
his own public humiliation
was Jack's intention.

15:32.125 --> 15:34.250
There's something deeper
going on there.

15:34.250 --> 15:35.583
Like?

15:35.583 --> 15:38.333
Like maybe you
should talk to him.

15:39.708 --> 15:40.959
About what?

15:42.083 --> 15:43.959
Well, for starters,
about the poem.

15:43.959 --> 15:50.250
-Maybe it wasn't misinterpreted.
- I'm--- No. No.

15:50.250 --> 15:51.250
Jack is not gay.

15:51.250 --> 15:53.542
He's talked about girls
his entire life.

15:53.542 --> 15:57.250
He's crazy about Joey.
He hates Madonna. He's not gay.

15:57.250 --> 16:01.959
- Have you ever asked him?
- No... And I don't need to.

16:04.458 --> 16:06.125
Ok, well,
hypothetically speaking,

16:06.125 --> 16:10.250
if Jack were gay...
How would that make you feel?

16:12.917 --> 16:18.959
- I guess I'd be disappointed.
- Disappointed? Jeez, Andie.

16:19.458 --> 16:20.458
[HUFFS LOUDLY ANNOYED]

16:20.708 --> 16:24.917
You asked me how I'd feel.
I don't need this, ok?

16:24.917 --> 16:28.083
I don't need to be attacked
over some hypothetical feeling

16:28.083 --> 16:30.041
about a hypothetical situation

16:30.041 --> 16:33.125
that is completely
and totally unfathomable.

16:33.125 --> 16:36.000
Well, for his sake,
I hope you're right.

16:36.792 --> 16:37.792
[SIGHS]

16:38.959 --> 16:41.125
[PHONE RINGING]

16:41.417 --> 16:42.667
JEN: Hello?

16:42.667 --> 16:45.375
TY: What if I didn't ask you out
on a date, per se?

16:45.375 --> 16:48.000
Then you wouldn't
have to worry about
our inevitable breakup

16:48.000 --> 16:49.417
due to ideological
difficulties,

16:49.417 --> 16:51.000
and you could still
go out with me,

16:51.000 --> 16:53.458
non-Bible-related,
though, I promise.

16:54.375 --> 16:55.417
Sorry, Ty.

16:55.417 --> 16:57.417
Aw, Jen, have
a little faith in me.

16:57.417 --> 17:01.166
Maybe underneath
this Sunday school veneer
lies a partying maniac.

17:01.166 --> 17:03.333
I doubt it. I'm hanging up.

17:06.916 --> 17:08.416
[PHONE RINGS]

17:11.583 --> 17:13.333
TY: I told you I was persistent.

17:13.333 --> 17:15.250
You know, "persistent"
isn't exactly the word

17:15.250 --> 17:16.625
that comes to mind
right now.

17:16.625 --> 17:18.791
Come on, Jen.
I'll pick you up at 9:00.

17:18.791 --> 17:19.708
No.

17:24.040 --> 17:25.750
[PHONE RINGS]

17:26.375 --> 17:29.500
Nine forty five going once,
going twice...

17:29.500 --> 17:31.291
You really are persistent.

17:31.291 --> 17:34.208
Hey, come on, Jen.
Just a couple of hours.

17:37.000 --> 17:38.333
Be here at 10:00.

17:41.583 --> 17:44.417
Hey, Jo. Did you get the
cleaning supplies
for the kitchen?

17:44.417 --> 17:46.125
- Got them right here.
- Great.

17:46.125 --> 17:49.583
Uh, here. I can--
Let me take that in the back.

17:50.834 --> 17:53.291
He has been quiet
as a church mouse all night.

17:53.291 --> 17:55.959
- What happened?
- You don't even want to know.

17:55.959 --> 17:58.000
Poor guy. He looks like
he lost his best friend.

17:58.000 --> 18:00.583
- Go talk to him.
- Yeah, but he doesn't want to.

18:00.583 --> 18:02.708
I mean, how do you talk to
somebody about something

18:02.708 --> 18:05.708
that they've made
perfectly clear
they don't want to talk about?

18:05.708 --> 18:08.625
Well, I always start
with, "Long day, huh?"

18:08.625 --> 18:12.417
That opens the conversation up.
Well, I'm all through here.

18:12.417 --> 18:15.041
If you could lock up,
that'd be great. see ya!

18:15.041 --> 18:15.875
Ok.

18:27.583 --> 18:31.417
- Long day, huh?
- If you wanna ask me something,

18:31.417 --> 18:32.917
I suggest you just ask it.

18:33.417 --> 18:36.417
Look, I'm sorry, Jack.
It's just, you know,

18:36.417 --> 18:38.667
people are already
saying things.

18:39.917 --> 18:42.041
Since when do you care
what people are saying?

18:42.041 --> 18:43.583
That's not like you.

18:46.583 --> 18:50.500
Well, maybe it's because
you still haven't offered me
any kind of explanation

18:50.500 --> 18:51.917
for what you wrote.

18:53.208 --> 18:54.500
I don't have to.

18:56.667 --> 19:01.834
You're right. You don't.
Um... It's just that, you know,

19:02.333 --> 19:03.792
being the one
that you are dating,

19:03.792 --> 19:06.834
it'd be nice to know if there
was a particular reason

19:06.834 --> 19:08.959
why you did write
a poem about a guy.

19:09.750 --> 19:13.250
I mean, a poem that obviously
has some degree of importance
in your life,

19:13.250 --> 19:15.667
considering it did make you cry

19:15.667 --> 19:17.583
in front of a room
full of people.

19:19.667 --> 19:21.792
All right, look, um...

19:22.959 --> 19:25.792
I sat down last night
before I went to bed,

19:25.792 --> 19:28.500
and for a half an hour,
I wrote what I was feeling.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.125
And one of the images
that came into my head--
it was masculine.

19:31.125 --> 19:33.083
Nothing sexual about it, ok?

19:33.083 --> 19:36.500
It could have been me.
It could have been the image
of my brother.

19:36.500 --> 19:37.792
I don't know, Joey,

19:38.333 --> 19:41.333
but I do know that
there was nothing gay
about that poem.

19:46.875 --> 19:51.500
And as for the crying,
I don't know.

19:51.500 --> 19:53.625
It hit a weird nerve
when I started reading it.

19:55.375 --> 19:56.959
It just unleashed
some of the stuff

19:56.959 --> 19:58.500
that I've been dealing with
with my family

19:58.500 --> 20:00.250
and my brother's death...

20:01.000 --> 20:03.917
It's the only explanation
that I have, and if it's
not good enough for you,

20:03.917 --> 20:08.542
then you can just believe
what everybody else is saying.

20:09.291 --> 20:10.708
Look, Jack...

20:13.542 --> 20:14.875
I don't believe them.

20:17.542 --> 20:18.625
I hope not.

20:20.542 --> 20:24.875
Because I adore you,
Joey, and I assure you,

20:24.875 --> 20:27.125
if I was to ever
to write a love poem,

20:27.125 --> 20:30.875
it'd be about you.
Nobody else.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.041
TY: I think you're really
gonna like this place.

20:41.041 --> 20:44.083
JEN: If I'd known we
were going to a club,
I'd have brought my fake ID.

20:44.083 --> 20:45.208
- TY: Sherry.
- SHERRY: Hey.

20:45.208 --> 20:47.208
Good evening.
So are you singing tonight?

20:47.208 --> 20:49.250
Yeah. I'm up next. Any requests?

20:49.250 --> 20:53.708
Yeah. Um... Something romantic.
And two martinis.

20:53.708 --> 20:55.083
You got it, Ty.

20:55.083 --> 20:56.083
Thanks.

20:56.083 --> 20:57.333
Have a seat?

20:58.291 --> 20:59.708
Hey, Dean-o, baby.

21:00.375 --> 21:02.750
Isn't this a little bit
against the rules?

21:02.750 --> 21:04.125
Whose rules?

21:05.583 --> 21:08.250
Drinking, the whole
swinger lifestyle.

21:09.083 --> 21:11.458
I mean, it's not exactly
Sunday school clean.

21:11.875 --> 21:13.542
Sure, but...

21:13.542 --> 21:15.875
Right now, we're
not in Sunday school.

