22:26.500 --> 22:31.708
- It's that simple.
- Why are you doing this to me?

22:32.458 --> 22:34.041
Because he can.

22:35.708 --> 22:39.000
Mr. Witter, I recommend
you sit down.

22:39.000 --> 22:41.375
- No.
- I said, sit down!

22:41.375 --> 22:43.583
You want somebody
to read the poem, I'll read it.

22:44.500 --> 22:45.542
"Today."

22:45.542 --> 22:46.667
Ahem.

22:46.667 --> 22:49.542
"Today was a day the world
got smaller, darker,

22:49.542 --> 22:50.834
"I grew more afraid,

22:50.834 --> 22:53.000
Not of what I am,
but of what I could be--"

22:53.000 --> 22:55.125
Stop this instant. I said, stop!

22:55.125 --> 22:59.000
You will listen to me
when I talk to you, young man!

22:59.000 --> 22:59.959
Why should I?

22:59.959 --> 23:04.750
Oh, that's it.
I am writing you a pass.

23:05.125 --> 23:08.750
You can report immediately
to Principal Markey's office.

23:08.750 --> 23:11.250
What part of you
is it that gets off on
torturing your students?

23:11.250 --> 23:13.417
Everybody else in this classroom
may be afraid of you,

23:13.417 --> 23:14.208
but I'm not!

23:14.834 --> 23:17.375
I see your miserable
scare tactics for
exactly what they are,

23:17.375 --> 23:20.250
the misguided lashings
of a bitter, lonely old man

23:20.250 --> 23:23.375
who only feels good
when somebody else in
the class feels worse.

23:23.375 --> 23:25.083
Thank you, for the analysis,
Mr. Witter.

23:25.083 --> 23:28.625
I'll send a check along
with the "F" you'll get
on your report card.

23:28.625 --> 23:29.959
You can't fail me.

23:29.959 --> 23:32.041
I've gotten a "B" or better
on every test in this class!

23:32.041 --> 23:35.291
Hell I can't. I've been waiting
to fail you all quarter.

23:36.208 --> 23:37.458
You disgust me.

23:37.458 --> 23:40.083
And you, Mr. Witter,
are a failure,

23:40.083 --> 23:43.083
destined to always
be a failure.

23:43.083 --> 23:45.625
Trying to teach people like you

23:45.625 --> 23:48.708
is like spitting in
the face of the entire
educational system!

23:48.708 --> 23:51.166
No, sir.
That  is spitting in the face

23:51.166 --> 23:53.125
of the entire
educational system.

23:55.875 --> 23:57.375
[DOOR SLAMS]

24:17.417 --> 24:21.000
- I won't apologize.
- Yes, you will, Pacey.

24:22.000 --> 24:24.625
- No, I won't.
- What did I tell you?

24:24.625 --> 24:26.625
The child's an insubordinate
little waste.

24:26.625 --> 24:28.583
Ray, you're hardly
innocent here.

24:28.583 --> 24:31.458
- And what does that mean?
- You made a student cry.

24:31.458 --> 24:33.667
Another student had
an excessive reaction.

24:33.667 --> 24:37.708
You call a student spitting
in a teacher's face excessive?

24:37.708 --> 24:39.667
That's the understatement
of the year.

24:39.667 --> 24:42.625
PRINCIPAL MARKEY:
I suggest we reconvene tomorrow.

24:42.625 --> 24:45.458
Mr. Witter,
hopefully by that time,

24:45.458 --> 24:48.458
you will have been capable of
conjuring up an apology.

24:48.458 --> 24:53.083
If not, I will have no choice
but to put you on suspension.

24:58.917 --> 25:00.583
[DOORS OPEN]

25:01.125 --> 25:02.375
PACEY: Hey, Jack.

25:03.208 --> 25:05.291
Listen, man, you didn't
have to come down here.

25:05.291 --> 25:06.333
I mean, I appreciate it, but--

25:06.333 --> 25:08.834
I didn't.
Milo wants to talk to me.

25:08.834 --> 25:10.333
I can only imagine what about.

25:10.333 --> 25:13.000
Yeah. They wanted me
to apologize in there.

25:13.291 --> 25:15.000
I told them
to go screw themselves.

25:16.000 --> 25:17.000
That was stupid.

25:17.000 --> 25:18.834
Whose side are you
on here, anyway?

25:18.834 --> 25:21.583
My own, all right?
I can handle my own battles.

25:21.583 --> 25:23.458
I didn't need you
to make a spectacle
of this whole thing.

25:23.458 --> 25:26.041
Stop right there, Jack.
I thought I was helping you out.

25:26.041 --> 25:28.834
Yeah? Well, you weren't.
I didn't need a hero.

25:28.834 --> 25:31.166
I recognize it's
an addiction of yours,
but this is one instance

25:31.166 --> 25:33.458
where you should have
just kept your nose out of it.

25:38.250 --> 25:40.959
Well, we weren't selling roses.
Cupcake?

25:41.333 --> 25:45.375
- Thank you.
- Mm. So, full report.

25:45.375 --> 25:48.166
Tell me, was I
not fun last night?

25:48.166 --> 25:49.625
[CHUCKLING]

25:49.625 --> 25:52.250
- What's so funny?
- You. This.

25:52.250 --> 25:55.041
- What?
- The alternate identities.

25:55.708 --> 25:59.083
Ah, you mean student by day,
rat packer by night?

25:59.083 --> 26:01.708
Some people would call it
the height of hypocrisy.

26:01.708 --> 26:05.208
That's not hypocritical at all.
To me, it's, uh...

26:05.208 --> 26:08.166
Well, it's something to go
to church about on Sunday.

26:09.375 --> 26:11.875
Listen, my religion
doesn't assume

26:11.875 --> 26:14.083
that I'm a perfect
individual, Jen.

26:14.083 --> 26:16.375
In fact,
it expects that I'm not.

26:16.875 --> 26:21.083
I see, so it's a party-now,
confess-later sort of thing?

26:23.375 --> 26:24.834
You want to do it again?

26:26.917 --> 26:28.750
Come on.
Your Grams likes me.

26:28.750 --> 26:31.250
My Grams likes what
she knows about you,

26:31.250 --> 26:33.250
which, apparently,
isn't all that much.

26:33.834 --> 26:36.250
And you plan on
keeping it that way.

26:38.542 --> 26:39.750
That's a thought.

26:44.667 --> 26:47.542
- So what are you gonna do?
- What do you mean?

26:47.542 --> 26:49.959
Well, about Peterson?
you're gonna apologize, right?

26:49.959 --> 26:52.000
No. I'm gonna
take the suspension.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.291
What?
Why would you do that?

26:54.291 --> 26:55.583
Because, after
what that man did,

26:55.583 --> 26:56.959
I'm not gonna
apologize to him.

26:56.959 --> 26:58.083
He doesn't deserve it.

26:58.083 --> 27:00.291
No. It doesn't matter
what he did, Pacey.

27:00.291 --> 27:03.041
- You spit in his face.
- I was there, thank you.

27:04.125 --> 27:05.125
Dawson?

27:07.917 --> 27:10.291
- You, too, huh?
- Pacey, this is serious.

27:10.291 --> 27:11.291
You think I don't know that?

27:11.792 --> 27:13.417
All we're saying is
make sure you're aware
of the consequences.

27:13.417 --> 27:15.041
I am aware of
the consequences, all right?

27:15.417 --> 27:18.166
These are pamphlets Milo
coincidentally happened
to have on his desk.

27:18.625 --> 27:21.125
You ever feel like
you're trapped in one
of those lifetime movies?

27:21.917 --> 27:22.875
"Gay and ok."

27:22.875 --> 27:24.500
"What's your sexuality.
Am I gay?"

27:24.500 --> 27:26.708
God, it sounds
like one bad game show.

27:27.542 --> 27:28.542
What about your grade point?

27:28.542 --> 27:29.959
You still care
about that, don't you?

27:29.959 --> 27:32.959
It's not gonna survive
a suspension, Pacey.

27:32.959 --> 27:34.959
It'll destroy all the hard work
you've done,

27:34.959 --> 27:36.792
and you'll be right back
at square one.

27:36.792 --> 27:40.083
- An academic loser.
- That's not what I said.

27:40.083 --> 27:41.291
But it's what you felt.

27:41.291 --> 27:43.959
Andie, everything
that I've worked for,

27:43.959 --> 27:45.458
what you have helped me
to become

27:45.458 --> 27:47.750
is somebody
who believes in himself
and in his instincts,

27:47.750 --> 27:50.333
and every single one
of my instincts tells me

27:50.333 --> 27:53.083
that what that man did
in that classroom is wrong.

27:53.083 --> 27:54.500
It's just wrong.

27:58.917 --> 28:00.333
Oh, my God.

28:04.000 --> 28:05.583
I'm gonna need your help
with this, Joey.

28:05.583 --> 28:09.333
I have a feeling
it's gonna get a lot worse
before it gets better.

28:10.417 --> 28:12.917
- I'm here.
- Thanks.

29:06.000 --> 29:08.041
- Kiss me.
- Why?

29:08.041 --> 29:09.166
Just because.

29:38.250 --> 29:39.875
Thanks for cleaning up.

29:41.875 --> 29:42.792
Dialogue.

29:43.083 --> 29:45.500
That would mean you're talking
to me again, correct?

29:46.417 --> 29:49.917
Um, I've been really unfair
the past few days.

29:50.500 --> 29:53.208
Well, it's ok. I
knew you'd come around.

29:54.875 --> 29:57.291
Do you have to be
so immensely forgiving?

29:57.291 --> 30:00.125
I mean, don't you have
an ounce of meanness
anywhere in your body?

30:00.125 --> 30:03.959
At the very least it would
make our sibling squabbles
more interesting.

30:03.959 --> 30:07.291
Well, I don't need them
to be more interesting.
I win them as they are.

30:11.750 --> 30:15.291
It's just, um...
It's been really hard.

30:16.708 --> 30:18.000
For both of us.

30:18.959 --> 30:22.083
Yeah, but, you're better suited
for this sort of thing.

30:22.083 --> 30:25.417
Yeah, but no one's suited
for public ridicule, Andie.
You just deal with it.

30:27.417 --> 30:28.375
I don't.

30:29.500 --> 30:32.625
When I first heard
what happened to you in class,

30:33.125 --> 30:36.583
my, um, initial reaction...

30:38.417 --> 30:40.166
Was resentment.

30:41.208 --> 30:42.166
[CLEARS THROAT]

30:42.166 --> 30:43.333
Of all the possibilities,
you know,

30:43.333 --> 30:44.708
I didn't even
feel sorry for you.

30:44.708 --> 30:47.792
I just-- I thought,
"Oh, great, thanks.
You know,

30:47.792 --> 30:50.500
"just when things seemed
to be slowing down
in my life,

30:50.500 --> 30:52.667
and now I have to
deal with this."

30:53.792 --> 30:56.291
And as much as I love you, Jack,
it's just...

30:56.792 --> 30:59.041
Everything that has happened
to us in our lives

30:59.041 --> 31:00.875
has made me so afraid,

31:01.333 --> 31:02.667
and I just didn't
think that anybody

31:02.667 --> 31:04.250
could understand that,
especially you.

31:04.250 --> 31:07.417
I mean, you're so strong
and independent,
and then...

31:07.792 --> 31:09.083
And then...

31:09.375 --> 31:13.959
I read this.
It's, um, your poem.

31:14.375 --> 31:17.458
I kept one of the ones
that I tore down.

31:18.792 --> 31:21.625
It's a really beautiful
poem, Jack.

31:23.667 --> 31:26.041
And I don't know if it means
that you're gay or not,

31:26.041 --> 31:28.291
and, you know what,
I really don't care.

31:29.500 --> 31:31.834
But I'll tell you
what I do know.

31:33.208 --> 31:35.291
The person who wrote
this poem...

31:36.959 --> 31:39.000
He's just as scared
as I am...

31:43.166 --> 31:45.041
Jack, you're terrified,
and I'm your sister,

31:45.041 --> 31:46.875
and I had no idea.

31:47.333 --> 31:49.375
And I just want you
to know that...

31:50.375 --> 31:54.250
I'm here for you
and that I love you...

31:55.291 --> 31:56.708
And you're not alone.

32:07.917 --> 32:09.083
Thank you.

32:41.875 --> 32:45.125
- Dawson, can I come in?
- Oh! Um... Yeah.

32:45.125 --> 32:47.458
Sorry. I didn't mean
to surprise you. It's just--

32:47.458 --> 32:49.125
it's been a highly
irregular few days,

32:49.125 --> 32:51.625
and climbing this ladder
is the surest form of
normalcy that I know,

32:51.625 --> 32:56.250
and also I just wanted to say
I'm sorry about yesterday.

32:56.875 --> 33:02.208
- That's ok. I understand.
- Wow! This is amazing.

33:02.208 --> 33:04.750
- This is the whole town.
- It's incredible, isn't it.

33:04.750 --> 33:06.458
Jack built it just for the film.

33:08.125 --> 33:09.792
Ok. um...

33:12.000 --> 33:13.166
Dawson,
I need your advice,

33:13.166 --> 33:15.125
and I know
because of the situation

33:15.125 --> 33:17.333
it may be hard for you
to dispense it, but...

33:18.291 --> 33:23.041
- I really need it.
- Anything. Talk to me.

33:25.000 --> 33:29.792
Well, um, I'm thinking
that maybe...

33:30.500 --> 33:32.917
Maybe you were right
about, um,

33:34.708 --> 33:36.333
Jack and the poem.

33:37.917 --> 33:39.500
That he meant to write it.

33:39.500 --> 33:41.500
Well, he says he didn't,
and...

33:41.500 --> 33:44.000
You know, he has a thousand
reasonable excuses

33:44.000 --> 33:46.083
that all make sense.
It's just...

33:47.875 --> 33:49.583
They don't make sense.

33:50.542 --> 33:53.166
I just keep wishing that
I had done what you told me.

33:53.166 --> 33:54.834
If I just would've
asked him if--

33:57.166 --> 34:00.667
- If he was gay, um...
- Then why don't you?

34:00.959 --> 34:03.333
If I do that, then he'll know
that I've considered it,

34:03.333 --> 34:05.375
and if he knows that
I've considered it,

34:05.375 --> 34:08.208
then it'll always be there
that I've considered it, and...

34:09.708 --> 34:11.417
It's the elephant-in-the-room
syndrome--

34:12.375 --> 34:14.041
the obvious but unspoken
topic,

34:14.041 --> 34:17.500
the thing that's always lurking
but never brought up.

34:17.500 --> 34:18.542
[SIGHS]

34:18.542 --> 34:20.792
Of course, in your case
it's a gay elephant.

34:22.208 --> 34:26.166
- You know, this isn't funny.
- Even so, I had to say that.

34:27.875 --> 34:34.000
You have to ask him.
You know, I mean, look...

34:36.125 --> 34:38.542
It is one thing I've learned
about relationships
in the past year,

34:38.542 --> 34:40.208
it's that they begin
and end with honesty.

34:40.208 --> 34:42.250
If you want to save
what you have with Jack,

34:42.250 --> 34:46.958
and you believe that it's worth
saving, you gotta be honest.

34:48.625 --> 34:52.542
- You know?
- Yes.

34:53.458 --> 34:54.625
So, um...

34:56.000 --> 35:00.041
So, go...
Go hunt an elephant.

35:04.417 --> 35:07.291
Right. Thanks.

35:11.375 --> 35:12.458
Thank you.

35:20.417 --> 35:21.375
Yeah.

35:28.708 --> 35:31.959
[CLASS BELL RINGS]

35:45.375 --> 35:47.417
Oh, look at that guy.

35:47.417 --> 35:50.083
Tell me that is not somebody
who has it out for me.

35:50.959 --> 35:52.917
If he didn't before,
he sure does now.

35:55.125 --> 35:58.083
[SIGHS] You know,
maybe I should just do it.

35:58.083 --> 35:59.417
Just apologize.

36:02.000 --> 36:04.125
You don't think what I did
is right, do you?

36:05.208 --> 36:07.250
I can't judge. I wasn't there.

36:07.250 --> 36:09.041
But would you have
done it yourself?

36:12.625 --> 36:13.542
No.

36:18.667 --> 36:21.166
And if I go in there
and I can't apologize...

36:23.542 --> 36:25.000
Would you be ashamed of me?

36:26.500 --> 36:29.875
In my lifetime, Pacey,
I will never be ashamed of you.

36:32.583 --> 36:36.000
Pacey. We're ready for you.

36:41.500 --> 36:42.875
[CLEARING THROAT]

36:53.917 --> 36:57.041
Mr. Witter, I trust
you have had ample time

36:57.041 --> 37:00.375
to put into proper perspective
the events of yesterday morning?

37:01.667 --> 37:02.625
I have, yeah.

37:02.625 --> 37:04.333
Well, then, the ball's
in your court.

37:04.333 --> 37:05.583
We're all ears.

37:06.875 --> 37:08.959
I should start by saying
that I'm more ashamed

37:08.959 --> 37:10.583
by what I did in that
classroom yesterday

37:10.583 --> 37:12.750
than of anything I've ever done
in my entire life.

37:12.750 --> 37:16.166
It was flat wrong,
and I have no case here,
and I'm sorry...

37:16.667 --> 37:17.750
For the event.

37:18.375 --> 37:22.208
But I am not now,
nor will I ever be
apologetic for its intention.

37:23.041 --> 37:27.250
Every day, we, the students
of Capeside, come to a place
where you guys are in charge.

37:27.250 --> 37:30.959
You tell us when to arrive
and when to leave and when
to move rooms and when to eat.

37:30.959 --> 37:33.750
You tell us when we're doing
well and when we need
to be doing better,

37:33.750 --> 37:36.375
and we never, ever question it.
Because we're afraid to.

37:36.375 --> 37:38.583
Because to question it
is to go against the belief

37:38.583 --> 37:40.417
that the entire system
is built upon:

37:40.417 --> 37:43.041
the belief that you guys
know what's right.

37:43.458 --> 37:44.917
And I am not afraid to tell you

37:44.917 --> 37:47.417
that what happened
in that classroom
yesterday was not right.

37:47.417 --> 37:50.083
To make a student cry,
to embarrass him,

37:50.083 --> 37:52.834
to strip him of his dignity
in front of his classmates
is not right.

37:52.834 --> 37:54.125
And while I respect this system,

37:54.125 --> 37:57.041
I do not respect men like you,
Mr. Peterson. I don't.

37:57.041 --> 38:00.083
I can't, and I never will.
Not after what you did.

38:05.083 --> 38:06.542
You have a good afternoon.

38:35.041 --> 38:36.333
How'd it go?

38:39.959 --> 38:41.542
As well as could be
imagined.

38:45.458 --> 38:47.166
They suspended me
for a week.

38:48.166 --> 38:50.333
Why'd you bother
coming down here?

38:51.458 --> 38:53.291
Because I care about you.

38:55.041 --> 38:58.333
- Do you?
- What kind of question is that?

38:58.959 --> 39:00.875
It's a reasonable one, Andie.

39:02.291 --> 39:04.875
Do you have any idea
what I went through today?

39:05.333 --> 39:07.125
How much I needed
your support?

39:08.542 --> 39:12.250
Pacey, I can't support
everything you do. I never will.

39:12.250 --> 39:14.333
I don't want you to agree
with every decision I ever make.

39:14.333 --> 39:16.291
The world would be
a boring place if you did,

39:16.291 --> 39:20.166
but what I am asking for
is to know that some way,

39:20.166 --> 39:21.917
somehow,
you're there for me.

39:23.083 --> 39:28.041
How dare you?
I challenge one action of yours,

39:28.041 --> 39:30.500
and you throw it in my face
like it's some sort of weakness?

39:30.500 --> 39:32.875
It's not just me.
You weren't there
for your brother Jack, either.

39:32.875 --> 39:35.083
Oh, yes, I was.
I apologized to him,

39:35.083 --> 39:36.708
and I came to apologize
to you, too,

39:36.708 --> 39:41.542
but for some reason
I was struggling with it
all the way down here.

39:41.542 --> 39:44.458
That reason has suddenly
become crystal clear.

39:44.458 --> 39:46.458
Jack is innocent, Pacey.

39:46.458 --> 39:50.458
What's happening to him
right now he has no control
over, but you--

39:50.458 --> 39:52.250
you knew what you were
doing in that classroom.

39:52.250 --> 39:53.375
What would you have me do,

39:53.375 --> 39:55.208
just stand there
and let Peterson do that to him

39:55.208 --> 39:57.208
- when I knew the whole time...
- There are other ways--

39:57.208 --> 40:01.083
that it was my fault, Andie?
It was my fault!

40:02.667 --> 40:05.208
Peterson knew that he couldn't
get the best of me,

40:05.208 --> 40:07.041
so he went after your brother.

40:08.000 --> 40:10.291
If I hadn't instigated him
that day...

40:11.959 --> 40:13.625
None of this would've ever
happened.

40:16.542 --> 40:18.542
That's why I had to stop it.

40:18.542 --> 40:21.542
However I could, I just--I had
to stop it.

40:22.333 --> 40:25.333
Why didn't you tell me
that you felt responsible?

40:27.083 --> 40:28.583
Because, Andie...

40:30.625 --> 40:32.417
You didn't want to
hear about it.

40:33.250 --> 40:35.500
You just wanted me
to clean up the mess.

40:37.417 --> 40:39.917
And there are some messes
you just have to live with.

40:44.750 --> 40:46.291
I'm gonna go home now.

40:53.875 --> 40:55.583
Do you want me to come with you?

40:57.917 --> 41:01.041
No. Not tonight.

41:16.750 --> 41:17.750
Hey, Jack.

41:18.250 --> 41:20.458
Hey, where you been?
I've been covering both shifts.

41:22.166 --> 41:25.834
- Are you gay?
- Excuse me?

41:28.375 --> 41:31.792
Are you gay?
I mean, you don't have
to answer right away.

41:31.792 --> 41:32.959
I just had to ask right away

41:33.250 --> 41:35.458
because it's been
building up in me
and there's no easy way

41:35.458 --> 41:37.792
for a girl to ask her boyfriend
if he's gay than to just ask.

41:37.792 --> 41:40.166
I know you already told me
that the poem wasn't about a guy

41:40.166 --> 41:42.041
but I feel like
when we discussed it,

41:42.041 --> 41:44.834
we never really discussed it,
and I never really asked.

41:44.834 --> 41:46.542
Feel free to answer
any minute now--

41:46.542 --> 41:50.750
No. No. I'm not gay.

41:54.625 --> 41:56.166
Ok. Uh...

41:57.000 --> 41:59.208
You don't know
what a relief that is.

42:00.083 --> 42:01.333
I mean, not that I care,

42:01.333 --> 42:03.667
I would've dealt with it fine,
I promise. It's just...

42:04.250 --> 42:06.667
Who wants to deal
with all the obvious and
not so obvious issues

42:06.667 --> 42:11.542
of a girl who's dating a guy
who turns out to be gay?
And it's just so hard, and...

42:34.041 --> 42:35.458
Hey. Feel better now?

42:37.917 --> 42:39.458
You know, even though...

42:47.166 --> 42:50.583
- Could you do me a favor?
- Yeah, what?

42:52.959 --> 42:58.083
No more poems.
Just for a little while.

42:59.500 --> 43:00.750
You got it.

43:02.834 --> 43:04.041
No more poems.

43:27.250 --> 43:33.208
- I'm not gay, Joey. Ok?
- Yeah.

